---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Portugal Car Rental Booking Basics | TripAxle"
  description="Understand the booking terms, policies, and requirements that matter before reserving a rental car in Portugal."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Booking Basics</p>
    <h1>Booking Basics for Renting a Car in Portugal</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      Understand the booking terms, policies, and requirements that matter before you reserve.
      This section focuses on insurance, deposits, card rules, rental terms, and the details travelers should verify before booking.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="top-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>What this section covers</h2>
      <p>
        This section focuses on the contract and policy side of renting a car in Portugal,
        before pickup and before payment details turn into problems.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Insurance and coverage options</li>
        <li>Deposits, holds, and card requirements</li>
        <li>Rental terms and broker vs direct booking differences</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Planned page sections</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Portugal car rental insurance explained</li>
        <li>Deposits and card requirements</li>
        <li>Broker vs direct supplier</li>
        <li>How to read rental terms before booking</li>
        <li>Common car rental mistakes in Portugal</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="content-grid">
    <article class="main-card">
      <h2>What this section will help you understand</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>How insurance and coverage options usually work before booking</li>
        <li>What to verify about deposits, holds, and accepted cards</li>
        <li>How rental terms can vary between offers</li>
        <li>What to double-check before finalizing a reservation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to use this hub</h2>
      <p>
        Start here if you want to understand the booking terms behind the headline price.
        These guides are meant to help you interpret what you are agreeing to before you reserve,
        so you can compare offers more clearly and avoid common mistakes.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you already know the booking terms and need help with tolls, transmission choice,
        fuel, or pickup logistics, continue to the Practical Guides or the airport rental guides
        that match your trip.
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="side-card">
      <h2>Related Portugal pages</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/portugal-guide">Portugal Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/airport-rental-guides">Airport Rental Guides</a></li>
        <li><a href="/practical-guides">Practical Guides</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <style>
    .hero {
      padding: 2rem 0 2.25rem;
      max-width: 760px;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
      color: #2f6fed;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 5vw, 3.6rem);
      line-height: 1.08;
    }

    .intro {
      margin-top: 1rem;
      color: #5b5b55;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      max-width: 680px;
    }

    .top-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .content-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .card,
    .main-card,
    .side-card {
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid #e4e4de;
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 1.25rem;
    }

    h2 {
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
    }

    li + li {
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }

    .side-card a {
      color: #2f6fed;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .top-grid,
      .content-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>